         <abstract>
            <p>The computer can be especially useful for constructing foreign language and ESL tests from a data bank. Once established and saved to disk, the computer can quickly write a random order test complete with answer blanks and answer key. The program described here can serve as a template to create tests for many subjects and items, being easily modifiable by anyone with a modicum of programming experience.</p>
